comments: Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Neto's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.
Gafford (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Ingram (NOP) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Beal (WAS) pump fakes and lifts his pivot foot before returning to the ground to start his dribble.
Bledsoe (NOP) makes contact with Beal's (WAS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (WAS) is in the paint for about three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Gafford (WAS) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Williamson (NOP).

Gafford (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Williamson (NOP) and any follow-through contact to Williamson's arm or head after the release on his shot is deemed marginal.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
During the rebound, Williamson (NOP) places a resting hand on Gafford's (WAS) shoulder and marginal contact occurs as he dislodges the ball.
Adams (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Westbrook (WAS).
Williamson (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact on the dribble hand-off.
Hachimura (WAS) is moving alongside Ingram (NOP) and absorbs the contact created by Ingram during the driving shot attempt.
During the rebound, Gafford (WAS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Adams (NOP).
Bledsoe (NOP) legally contests Westbrook's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Before cleanly blocking the shot, Gafford (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position by collapsing his forearm into his body to absorb the contact during the driving shot attempt by Williamson (NOP).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is overturned to Pelicans ball.
Beal (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Ingram (NOP) at the end of the drive and makes clean ball contact on his dislodge attempt.
At the end of the drive, Westbrook (WAS) removes his resting forearm from Bledsoe's (NOP) front and any arm contact as they disengage is deemed marginal.
Adams (NOP) is deemed to be in the lane for about three seconds when the shot is imminent.
During the rebound, Adams (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Gafford (WAS) and Westbrook (WAS) cleanly recovers the loose ball. Westbrook immediately calls for and is granted his timeout request.
Ball (NOP) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Bledsoe (NOP) engages on the pick and marginal contact occurs as he immediately slides his hand off of Gafford's (WAS) waist.
Bledsoe (NOP) makes contact with Gafford's (WAS) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
Ingram (NOP) taps the ball back to his teammate Marshall (NOP) before any marginal contact with Neto (WAS) occurs as they come together.
Neto (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Marshall (NOP) and Marshall inadvertently steps on Neto's already planted foot.
Gafford (WAS) turns up court dribbling into Williamson (NOP) and marginal contact occurs that does not affect his ability to maintain possession of the ball.
Adams (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.

Gafford (WAS) establishes himself in a wide screening position in Marshall's (NOP) path and absorbs the majority of the contact to his chest. Any follow-through leg to leg contact as Marshall goes over the screen is deemed marginal and it does not affect his ability to maintain his legal guarding position.
Gafford (WAS) is in the paint for about three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Beal (WAS) establishes himself in Bledsoe's (NOP) path by firming up on his left foot to absorb any contact as Bledsoe goes under the pick.

During the dribble hand-off, Ingram (NOP) establishes himself in a wide screening position in Neto's (WAS) path and marginal leg to leg contact occurs. Neto is able to play through the contact and recover to his defensive matchup.
At the end of the drive, Hachimura (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Williamson (NOP) and absorbs the contact before Williamson throws his errant pass.
Adams (NOP) is deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.

Replay review of the foul called on Williamson (NOP) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Williamson (NOP) makes contact with Westbrook's (WAS) elbow, which affects his jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (WAS) and Neto (WAS) maintain legal guarding positions on Ingram (NOP) as he receives the inbounds pass and shoots from half court.
